<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-05T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-05T16:00:00-05:00" n="275" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/26284:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-05T22:00:00+01:00">December
                                    5, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 6—2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1969. Your 1362, December 4, 7 p.m. We have no evidence the reports are
                            true. Ministry of the Army denied similar reports last week. I am seeing
                            the Foreign Minister Monday<note n="73" xml:id="d275fn73">December
                                7.</note> and shall then discuss the matter with him.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>